					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3620901#post-3594900</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3620901/scp-3263#post-3594900</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 16 Sep 2017 12:55:30 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>TL333s</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1304786</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">YER A REALITY BENDER HARRY</span></p> <p>Starts out as &quot;Hogwarts in SCP land&quot;, then turns into &quot;Prometheus Labs preying on young mages via Harry Potter fantasies&quot; and then ends on a sad note. I'm honestly not sure why this is happening, though I suppose I can put together a few reasons. But it ends up coming off well. I particularly like the Foundation (of all people) critiquing the simulation as not real magic, and I really appreciate that you specifically call out Harry Potter. +1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
